            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3549417-kari-wainwright?shelf=favorite">favorite</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer705214459" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer575239629777682089">	Speak of the Devil takes the reader on a ride to a dark and dangerous place. A truly frightening aspect of the book is that author Allison Leotta bases some of her protagonist’s, Anna Curtis, cases on real-life ones from her prosecutorial days in the Washington, D.C. sex-crimes unit.<br/>	Just when Anna finds the courage to commit to Jack Bailey, the chief homicide prosecutor, she has to deal with life-threatening issues because of her job. Not to mention the gasp-inducing shock that occurs about tw</span>
  <span id="freeText575239629777682089" style="display:none">	Speak of the Devil takes the reader on a ride to a dark and dangerous place. A truly frightening aspect of the book is that author Allison Leotta bases some of her protagonist’s, Anna Curtis, cases on real-life ones from her prosecutorial days in the Washington, D.C. sex-crimes unit.<br />	Just when Anna finds the courage to commit to Jack Bailey, the chief homicide prosecutor, she has to deal with life-threatening issues because of her job. Not to mention the gasp-inducing shock that occurs about two-thirds of the way into the book. I can’t say more without causing a major spoiler.<br />	What I can say is that Leotta’s work keeps getting darker and grittier while remaining entertaining. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="575239629777682089" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


